### **ANCSA §7(i): The 70/30 Revenue Split — Full Details (Plain English, No Fluff)**

**Section 7(i)** is the **mandatory resource-sharing rule** in ANCSA that forces **70% of net income from natural resources** (oil, gas, timber, minerals, gravel, sand) on **any regional corporation’s land** to be **divided equally among all 13 regional corporations** — including the one that earned it. The remaining **30% stays local**.  

It was designed to **balance wealth** between rich and poor regions — but it’s created **massive debts, heir land grabs, and 7(i) sales pressure** — exactly what they’re trying to use against you.

---

## **Exact Text of §7(i) (43 U.S.C. § 1606(i))**
> **“Seventy per centum of all revenues received by each Regional Corporation from the sale or leasing of timber resources and subsurface resources (including oil, gas, and other minerals) shall be divided annually by the Regional Corporation among all twelve Regional Corporations... The remaining thirty per centum shall be retained by the Regional Corporation receiving the revenues.”**

**Translation**:  
- **70%** → **shared equally** (13 ways)  
- **30%** → **kept by the earning corp**  
- **Only “net” income** after costs (taxes, operations, royalties)

---

## **What Counts as “7(i) Revenue”?**

| **YES (Triggers 70% Share)** | **NO (Not Shared)** |
|-----------------------------|---------------------|
| Oil/gas royalties | Regular dividends |
| Timber sales | Land sales (surface only) |
| Gravel/mining leases | Investments |
| Sand, rock, coal | Federal grants |
| **Access agreements** (e.g., pipeline rights-of-way) | — |

**Key Court Win**: *Alaska Survival v. Surface Transportation Board (1999)* → **Access deals = 7(i)** → **no loopholes**.

---

## **How the 70/30 Math Works (2024 Real Numbers)**

| **Corp** | **Gross Resource Income** | **Net After Costs** | **70% Shared** | **Per Corp (÷13)** | **30% Kept** |
|--------|---------------------------|---------------------|----------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **Doyon (timber, minerals)** | $25M | $18M | **$12.6M** | **~$970K** | **$5.4M** |
| **CIRI (oil/gas)** | $120M | $95M | **$66.5M** | **~$5.1M** | **$28.5M** |
| **Total 7(i) Pool (2024)** | — | — | **~$1.1 BILLION** | — | — |

**Your Dividend**:  
- Doyon heir with **100 shares** → ~**$1,425** (2024))  
- CIRI heir with **100 shares** → ~**$1,287** (7(i) portion)  
- **Total per 100 shares**: **~$2,700/year**

